---
name: js-generator-next-option
backends: [int, js]
---

# generator.next() returns a real Option on JS (js-generator-next-option)

A pull-based `generator[T] { }`'s `next()` returned a bespoke `{_isSome,_value}`/null
shape on JS, which `_show` rendered as `[object Object]`/`null` instead of
`Some(v)`/`None` (and `next() match { case Some(v) => }` couldn't match it). It now
returns a real `Option`, matching the interpreter.

```scalascript
val g = generator[Int] { () =>
  suspend(10)
  suspend(20)
}
println(g.next())
println(g.next())
println(g.next())

val h = generator[Int] { () =>
  suspend(7)
}
h.next() match
  case Some(v) => println(s"got $v")
  case None    => println("empty")
```
